column5: Hi guys,  Heading up to Gloucester pool next week...hope to land some walleye..any pointers for that body of water? Promise to file a report if successful!  Thanks Skdds
We used to fish at the base of White's Falls decades back, but there are far too many swimmers there now to fish that spot.  Just have to search for the ledges and weed humps along the west shore.
Are your chances decent to hook a few eyes up there in a day??
thanks for the suggestion..I'm not too far from there and will check it out-skdds
